enhanced_by.reason: Both methods involve creating an unmodifiable view of a map, which sets up the state for the values() method to operate on.
The entrySet() method also returns an unmodifiable view of the map's entries, similar to how values() returns an unmodifiable view of the map's values.
The values() method returns an unmodifiable collection of values, which is directly comparable to the output of the unmodifiableCollection() method.
The keySet() method returns an unmodifiable set of keys, which can be used to assert the behavior of the values() method by comparing the sizes of the key set and value collection.
